@page "/story"

<PageTitle>Our Story</PageTitle>

<style>
    /* Comfy Viewport Animation Styles */
    .comfy-animate {
        opacity: 1;
        transform: translateY(0);
        /* Soft, easing curve for a relaxing, unhurried feel */
        transition: opacity 1.2s cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1), 
                    transform 1.2s cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1);
    }

    .comfy-animate.is-visible {
        opacity: 1;
        transform: translateY(0);
    }

    /* Slightly different animation for images to give a "breathing" effect */
    .comfy-animate-image {
        opacity: 1;
        transform: scale(1);
        transition: opacity 1.5s cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1), 
                    transform 1.5s cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1);
    }

    .comfy-animate-image.is-visible {
        opacity: 1;
        transform: scale(1);
    }

    /* Stagger delays for grouped elements */
    .delay-1 { transition-delay: 0.1s; }
    .delay-2 { transition-delay: 0.3s; }
    .delay-3 { transition-delay: 0.5s; }
</style>

<section class="hero editorial-hero editorial-hero--about story-intro">
    <div class="hero__content">
        <p class="eyebrow comfy-animate">Our Story</p>
        <h1 class="comfy-animate delay-1">Built for the quiet exchange between craft and care.</h1>
        <p class="lede comfy-animate delay-2">
            Artisanal Brew didn’t begin with a grand business plan. It began during a sudden Tuesday downpour, 
            a spilled bag of rye flour, and an extraordinarily opinionated stray orange tabby named Barnaby.
        </p>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="story-image story-image--wide comfy-animate-image delay-1"></section>

<section class="story-block story-block--asymmetric">
    <div class="comfy-animate">
        <p class="eyebrow">Founders</p>
        <h2>A room shaped by ritual.</h2>
    </div>
    <p class="comfy-animate delay-1">
        Julian was roasting beans next door when Elena, baking her grandmother’s sourdough before sunrise, accidentally dropped a 50lb bag of flour. 
        Julian brought over a freshly pulled espresso to help with the cleanup. Barnaby the cat immediately claimed the warm top of the 
        espresso machine as his bed. Sitting around the flour-dusted table, watching the storm pass, they realized coffee and bread—and the 
        time spent enjoying them—were simply better shared. 
    </p>
</section>

<section class="story-split">
    <div class="story-image story-image--portrait comfy-animate-image"></div>
    <div class="story-panel">
        <p class="eyebrow comfy-animate">Philosophy</p>
        <h2 class="comfy-animate delay-1">Nothing rushed, nothing crowded.</h2>
        <p class="comfy-animate delay-2">
            Every detail today honors that rainy morning. We source coffee for clarity and sweetness, bake in small batches, 
            and leave room between tables so conversation can settle naturally. The marble counters hold the morning light, 
            the ceramics have a comforting weight, and the menu only changes when the ingredients ask it to.
        </p>
        <a class="button button--ghost comfy-animate delay-3" href="visit">Plan a visit</a>
    </div>
</section>
